"n.卡路里；卡(热量单位) 【英】 卡路里(unit for measuring a quantity of heat)大卡,千卡(unit for measuring the energy value of food) 【考】 heat : calories / liquid : gallons / power : watt / sound : decibel / electricity : volt(卡路里是热量单位/ 加仑是液体体积单位/ 瓦是动力单位/分贝是 声音单位/伏特是电单位) 【记】 联系词根calori(热)c alorie(热卡) 【同】 派生词: calorific (adj. 生热的) n. 卡路里(热量单位, 音译词) 【例】She can eat only 1500 calories a day 她每天只能吃一千五百卡路里. 【参】calorific(adj 产生热量的) 【类】heat: calories = liquid: gallons = power: watt热量单位是卡路里 = 液体体积单位是加仑 = 功率单位是瓦特sound: decibel = electricity volt声音单位是分贝 = 电的单位是伏特 【记】译音卡路里,热量单位 calorie (n.)  1866, from French calorie, from Latin calor (genitive caloris) ""heat,"" from PIE *kle-os-, suffixed form of root *kele- (1) ""warm"" (cognates: Latin calidus ""warm,"" calere ""be hot;"" Sanskrit carad- ""harvest,"" literally ""hot time;"" Lithuanian silti ""become warm,"" silus ""August;"" Old Norse hlær, Old English hleow ""warm""). In scientific use, largely replaced 1950 by the joule. As a unit of energy, defined as ""heat required to raise 1 gram of water 1 degree Celsius"" (the small or gram calorie), but also as ""heat required to raise 1 kilogram of water 1 degree Celsius"" (the large calorie or kilocalorie)."
